        <p class="text-sm">
          Ghanaian cuisine is diverse and flavorful, featuring staples like rice, yams, and plantains, often paired with hearty stews and soups. Popular dishes include jollof rice, banku with okra soup, and fufu with light soup. Street foods like kelewele (spicy fried plantains) and grilled tilapia are also beloved.
        </p>
