        <p class="text-sm">
          Nigerian cuisine is rich and diverse, featuring staples like yams, cassava, and plantains, often paired with spicy stews and soups. Iconic dishes include Jollof rice and pounded yam with egusi soup, while street foods like suya and puff-puff are also popular. Bold and flavorful, Nigerian food reflects the country's vibrant cultural heritage.
        </p>
