          Italian cuisine is renowned for its regional diversity and rich flavors, with staples like pasta, olive oil, and tomatoes. Iconic dishes include pasta carbonara, risotto, and pizza Margherita, while desserts like tiramisu and gelato are world-famous. Fresh ingredients and simple preparation define this beloved culinary tradition.
